37-466.Aquaculture permit; rights.

A holder of an aquaculture permit may import aquatic organisms, lawfully held in possession in any other state or country, into this state except as provided in sections 37-547 to 37-550.

SourceLaws 1929, c. 112, VII, § 5, p. 439;C.S.1929, § 37-705;R.S.1943, § 37-705;Laws 1957, c. 139, § 19, p. 473;Laws 1967, c. 216, § 18, p. 591;Laws 1989, LB 34, § 45;Laws 1994, LB 1165, § 16;Laws 1995, LB 718, § 3;R.S.Supp.,1996, § 37-705;Laws 1998, LB 922, § 176;Laws 1999, LB 176, § 50.
